                        <interp inst="t18370508-name-731" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH BRIEZE</persName>
                  </hi>. I lived with my mother, Ann Brieze, in Windsor-street. The prisoner gave me that cloak to pawn on the 24th of April—I took it to Mr. Drew, the pawnbroker.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. She sent me for it—she said she had lived with a person that was a laundress, she took it, and ran with it directly, and had half the money. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. Yes, I had half the money.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
